UID:4eec73d93281c87567e5a5b871a1e57abd57f14e@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T162503Z
DTSTART:20260501T013000Z
DTEND:20260501T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Producer Price Indexes\, Australia\, March 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS latest release pag
 e\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Cha
 nge in prices received by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual
  market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the local cu
 rrency if traders expect producer inflation to flow through to consumer 
 inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an early signal of i
 nflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly
  in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less ma
 rket-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation is the mai
 n macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\nOfficial so
 urce: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflat
 ion/producer-price-indexes-australia/mar-2026
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation
