DTSTART:20260521T013000Z
DTEND:20260521T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Labour Force\, Australia\, April 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS latest release pag
 e\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Employment / Payrolls / Labour Force\n\n
 • Measures: Change in employment\, unemployment\, participation and la
 bour-market strength.\n\n• Usual market effect: Stronger-than-forecast
  jobs data is usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bon
 ds if it increases rate-hike expectations.\n\n• Why traders care: Jobs
  data is a major driver of interest-rate expectations\, consumer spendin
 g expectations and recession-risk pricing.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly.\n\
 n• Notes: For the US\, Non-Farm Payrolls is one of the most market-mov
 ing releases. For Australia\, Labour Force data is important for RBA exp
 ectations.\n\n• Acronyms: NFP = Non-Farm Payrolls\; ABS = Australian B
 ureau of Statistics\; BLS = Bureau of Labor Statistics.\nOfficial source
 : https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/labour/employment-and-unemployment/l
 abour-force-australia/apr-2026
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/labour/employment-and-unemployment/
 labour-force-australia/apr-2026
