UID:9713faec3edcbb8f047c2d17391af3cf9350cee8@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T162503Z
DTSTART:20260527T013000Z
DTEND:20260527T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia\, April 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS latest release pag
 e\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Cha
 nge in the prices paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services.\
 n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bu
 llish for the local currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may
  price in higher interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of 
 the most watched inflation indicators because it can quickly shift centr
 al-bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australi
 an CPI has both monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n
 \n• Notes: Core CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to 
 give a cleaner read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: C
 PI = Consumer Price Index.\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/stat
 istics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/consumer-price-index-australi
 a/apr-2026
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation
 /consumer-price-index-australia/apr-2026
