UID:520dc0ed3bf69515ad281b9a90533150ea66dd04@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T162503Z
DTSTART:20260528T123000Z
DTEND:20260528T130000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 US BEA: GDP (Second Estimate) and Corporate Profits\, 1st Qu
 arter 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: US BEA\nImpact: high\nwww.bea.gov\nExplainer:\n• Wh
 at it is: Gross Domestic Product\n\n• Measures: Broad change in the va
 lue of goods and services produced by the economy.\n\n• Usual market e
 ffect: Stronger-than-forecast GDP can be bullish for the local currency 
 and equities\, although the reaction depends on inflation and rate expec
 tations.\n\n• Why traders care: GDP is the broadest measure of economi
 c growth and helps traders judge whether the economy is accelerating or 
 slowing.\n\n• Frequency: Quarterly\, with revisions.\n\n• Notes: GDP
  can be backward-looking\, so markets often react more strongly when the
  result changes the outlook for central-bank policy or recession risk.\n
 \n• Acronyms: GDP = Gross Domestic Product.\nOfficial source: https://
 www.bea.gov/news/schedule/ics/online-calendar-subscription.ics
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.bea.gov/news/schedule/ics/online-calendar-subscription.ic
 s
