SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Labour Force\, Australia\, June 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page releas
 e date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Emplo
 yment / Payrolls / Labour Force\n\n• Measures: Change in employment\, 
 unemployment\, participation and labour-market strength.\n\n• Usual ma
 rket effect: Stronger-than-forecast jobs data is usually bullish for the
  local currency and bearish for bonds if it increases rate-hike expectat
 ions.\n\n• Why traders care: Jobs data is a major driver of interest-r
 ate expectations\, consumer spending expectations and recession-risk pri
 cing.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly.\n\n• Notes: For the US\, Non-Farm Pay
 rolls is one of the most market-moving releases. For Australia\, Labour 
 Force data is important for RBA expectations.\n\n• Acronyms: NFP = Non
 -Farm Payrolls\; ABS = Australian Bureau of Statistics\; BLS = Bureau of
  Labor Statistics.\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/l
 abour/employment-and-unemployment/labour-force-australia
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/labour/employment-and-unemployment/
 labour-force-australia
