UID:ce0a8dc824ed0cc21b4ae6756d3ecfb440021bde@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T162503Z
DTSTART:20260729T180000Z
DTEND:20260729T190000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficial Federal Reserve monthl
 y calendar FOMC meeting entry.\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank
  Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy statemen
 t and guidance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More h
 awkish-than-expected guidance is usually bullish for the local currency 
 and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is usually bea
 rish for the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Ce
 ntral-bank decisions directly affect interest rates\, currency valuation
 \, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled sev
 eral times per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not only to t
 he rate decision\, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, press confere
 nce and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RB
 A = Reserve Bank of Australia.\nOfficial source: https://www.federalrese
 rve.gov/newsevents/2026-july.htm
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-july.htm
