UID:45a693333d3aad90f7aa540261a1202e6a2d8995@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T162503Z
DTSTART:20260731T013000Z
DTEND:20260731T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Producer Price Indexes\, Australia\, June 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page releas
 e date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Produ
 cer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received by producers 
 for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast
  PPI can be bullish for the local currency if traders expect producer in
 flation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: 
 PPI can provide an early signal of inflation pressure before it reaches 
 consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\
 n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can st
 ill matter when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI 
 = Producer Price Index.\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statist
 ics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes-australia
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation
 /producer-price-indexes-australia
