SUMMARY:🔥 AU RBA: RBA Cash Rate Media Conference
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU RBA\nImpact: high\nOfficial RBA media conference f
 ollowing the cash rate decision. Manual official-date fallback included 
 so this event cannot disappear if the RBA page parser fails.\nExplainer:
 \n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-r
 ate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n
 • Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually 
 bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-e
 xpected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bon
 ds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect inte
 rest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\
 n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The ma
 rket often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the statem
 ent\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Fed
 eral Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\nOfficial 
 source: https://www.rba.gov.au/schedules-events/calendar/
