UID:fbbf336fa5d2fcbd6e7fdcfa4a47c3ef976eb9e2@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T162503Z
DTSTART:20260813T013000Z
DTEND:20260813T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Average Weekly Earnings\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\nExplainer:\n
 • What it is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings\n\n• Measures: Cha
 nge in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forec
 ast wage growth can be bullish for the local currency if traders expect 
 stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-bank policy.\n\n• Why 
 traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation and is closely watched
  by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quarterly depending on r
 elease.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive for consumers but can
  also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage Price Ind
 ex.\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-rel
 eases/202608
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202608
