SUMMARY:🔥 US BEA: Personal Income and Outlays\, July 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: US BEA\nImpact: high\nwww.bea.gov\nExplainer:\n• Wh
 at it is: Core PCE Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices paid by
  consumers for goods and services\, excluding food and energy.\n\n• Us
 ual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for
  USD and bearish for bonds\, because it can increase expectations of tig
 hter Federal Reserve policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Core PCE is one of
  the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation measures\, so it can strongly
  influence interest-rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly\, usual
 ly released about four weeks after the month ends.\n\n• Notes: Core PC
 E differs from Core CPI because it uses a different basket and weighting
  method. CPI often gets more immediate market attention\, but Core PCE i
 s very important for Fed policy.\n\n• Acronyms: PCE = Personal Consump
 tion Expenditures\; CPI = Consumer Price Index.\nOfficial source: https:
 //www.bea.gov/news/schedule/ics/online-calendar-subscription.ics
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.bea.gov/news/schedule/ics/online-calendar-subscription.ic
