SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Australian National Accounts: National Income\, Expe
 nditure and Product\, June 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page releas
 e date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Gross
  Domestic Product\n\n• Measures: Broad change in the value of goods an
 d services produced by the economy.\n\n• Usual market effect: Stronger
 -than-forecast GDP can be bullish for the local currency and equities\, 
 although the reaction depends on inflation and rate expectations.\n\n•
  Why traders care: GDP is the broadest measure of economic growth and he
 lps traders judge whether the economy is accelerating or slowing.\n\n•
  Frequency: Quarterly\, with revisions.\n\n• Notes: GDP can be backwar
 d-looking\, so markets often react more strongly when the result changes
  the outlook for central-bank policy or recession risk.\n\n• Acronyms:
  GDP = Gross Domestic Product.\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/
 statistics/economy/national-accounts/australian-national-accounts-nation
 al-income-expenditure-and-product
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
