SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia\, August 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page releas
 e date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Consu
 mer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the prices paid by consumers 
 for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-t
 han-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the local currency and bea
 rish for bonds\, because markets may price in higher interest rates.\n\n
 • Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indicator
 s because it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n• Fr
 equency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indicator re
 leases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes volati
 le items such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on underlying in
 flation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\nOfficial
  source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inf
 lation/consumer-price-index-australia
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation
 /consumer-price-index-australia
