UID:98dd600792636311665826250295ee6689d5ec7f@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T162503Z
DTSTART:20261119T003000Z
DTEND:20261119T010000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Labour Force\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\nExplainer:\n
 • What it is: Employment / Payrolls / Labour Force\n\n• Measures: Ch
 ange in employment\, unemployment\, participation and labour-market stre
 ngth.\n\n• Usual market effect: Stronger-than-forecast jobs data is us
 ually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds if it increas
 es rate-hike expectations.\n\n• Why traders care: Jobs data is a major
  driver of interest-rate expectations\, consumer spending expectations a
 nd recession-risk pricing.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly.\n\n• Notes: For 
 the US\, Non-Farm Payrolls is one of the most market-moving releases. Fo
 r Australia\, Labour Force data is important for RBA expectations.\n\n
 • Acronyms: NFP = Non-Farm Payrolls\; ABS = Australian Bureau of Stati
 stics\; BLS = Bureau of Labor Statistics.\nOfficial source: https://www.
 abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202611
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202611
