UID:9ba9b33453593497c1fc41d128767032289ba339@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T162503Z
DTSTART:20261125T003000Z
DTEND:20261125T010000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\nExplainer:\n
 • What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the pric
 es paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual ma
 rket effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the l
 ocal currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may price in highe
 r interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watche
 d inflation indicators because it can quickly shift central-bank rate ex
 pectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both
  monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Co
 re CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner 
 read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer P
 rice Index.\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/fu
 ture-releases/202611
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202611
